o Charles Dennis) across five generations."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Married widow Katharine Sanders Varnum, 1885","body":"Charles Dennis married Katharine Corse Sanders Varnum on June 2, 1885 in Manhattan New York — she had previously been married to Robert Taylor Varnum. The couple had three children together: Hamilton Ingersoll (1888-1940), Anita Ingersoll Gwynne (1891-1970), and Justine Ingersoll Arnold (1893-1984). His grandchildren through these three children form the documented twentieth-century Ingersoll-Arnold-Gwynne descendants of the original Connecticut bar family."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"New Haven 1843 to Manhattan 1905, Green-Wood Cemetery","body":"Charles Dennis Ingersoll was born January 15, 1843 in New Haven Connecticut and died January 8, 1905 in Manhattan New York at age sixty-one. He is buried at Green-Wood Cemetery in Greenwood Heights Brooklyn New York — breaking the Ingersoll family Grove Street Cemetery tradition through his NYC career. His wife Katharine died in Menton France in 1922."}],"quotes":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"military_service":[],"education":[],"career":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Judge Charles Dennis Ingersoll","first_name":"Charles","last_name":"Ingersoll","middle_name":"Dennis","married_names":[],"title":"Judge","gender":"male"},"slug":"charles-ingersoll-1843"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"HD5129","slug":"charles-ingersoll-1843","n":"Judge Charles Dennis Ingersoll","by":1843,"dy":1905,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":8},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"I01303","slug":"katharine-sanders-1861","n":"Katharine Corse Ingersoll","by":1861,"dy":1922,"sx":"u","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":1885,"children":[{"id":"HD5132","slug":"hamilton-ingersoll-1888","n":"Hamilton Ingersoll","by":1888,"dy":1940,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":9},{"id":"HD5133","slug":"anita-gwynne-1891","n":"Anita 